---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import handheldNodeGutsOrum from "../assets/handheld-node-guts-Orum.jpg";
import handheldNodeGuts2Orum from "../assets/handheld-node-guts-2-Orum.jpg";
---

<Layout
	title="Getting Started"
	description="Learn how to join Madison Mesh: get hardware, install software, and send your first message on the mesh network."
>
	<div class="container">
		<section class="section">
			<h1>Getting Started</h1>
			<p>Everything you need to go from zero to sending your first message on the network.</p>
		</section>

		<!-- Step overview -->
		<section class="section" style="padding-top: 0;">
			<div class="steps">
				<!-- Step 1 -->
				<div class="step">
					<div class="step-number">1</div>
					<div class="step-body">
						<h3>Get hardware</h3>
						<p>
							You need a LoRa radio with a compatible chip (typically Semtech SX1262 or SX1276).
							Start with one of these options:
						</p>
						<p style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem;"><strong>Common portable prebuilt options:</strong></p>
						<ul style="color: var(--clr-light); padding-left: 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 1rem;">
							<li>
								<a href="https://lilygo.cc/en-us/products/t-deck" target="_blank"
									>Lilygo T-Deck</a
								>
							</li>
							<li>
								<a
									href="https://www.seeedstudio.com/SenseCAP-Card-Tracker-T1000-E-for-Meshtastic-p-5913.html"
									target="_blank">Seeed T1000-E</a
								>
							</li>
							<li>
								<a
									href="https://www.seeedstudio.com/Wio-Tracker-L1-Pro-p-6454.html"
									target="_blank">Seeed Wio L1 Pro</a
								>
							</li>
							<li>
								<a
									href="https://store.rakwireless.com/products/wismesh-tag-meshtastic-gps-lora-tracker-ip66"
									target="_blank">Rak WisMesh Tag</a
								>
							</li>
						</ul>
						<p style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem;"><strong>Good boards to build around:</strong></p>
						<ul style="color: var(--clr-light); padding-left: 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 1rem;">
							<li>
								<a href="https://heltec.org/project/wifi-lora-32-v4/" target="_blank"
									>Heltec V4</a
								>
							</li>
						</ul>
						<p class="text-muted">
							Ask in the Discord for current community recommendations &mdash; hardware evolves
							quickly!
						</p>
					</div>
				</div>

				<hr class="divider" />

				<!-- Step 2 -->
				<div class="step">
					<div class="step-number">2</div>
					<div class="step-body">
						<h3>Choose your technology</h3>
						<p>
							Madison Mesh currently supports two LoRa networking platforms. We recommend
							<strong>MeshCore</strong> for reliability, especially for text messaging. Meshtastic is
							better for smaller networks and having fun, and it's easier when starting out.
						</p>

						<div class="card-grid" style="margin-top: 1rem;">
							<div class="card">
								<h3 style="color: var(--clr-secondary);">MeshCore</h3>
								<p style="font-size: 0.9rem; margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">
									Best for <strong>text message communication</strong>. Only repeaters
									forward messages, which is more efficient at covering large areas and
									results in better reliability for messaging. This is our primary network.
								</p>
								<p class="text-muted" style="margin-bottom: 0;">
									<a href="https://meshcore.co.uk/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"
										>meshcore.co.uk &rarr;</a
									>
								</p>
							</div>
							<div class="card">
								<h3>Meshtastic</h3>
								<p style="font-size: 0.9rem; margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">
									Best for small or sparse networks. Nodes advertise more frequently, which
									makes it easier to see new nodes come online and get started, but it
									doesn't scale as well. Larger global community and more device options.
								</p>
								<p class="text-muted" style="margin-bottom: 0;">
									<a href="https://meshtastic.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"
										>meshtastic.org &rarr;</a
									>
								</p>
							</div>
						</div>

						<p style="margin-top: 1rem;" class="text-muted">
							NOTE: Both platforms support much of the same hardware, so your radio purchase
							generally won&rsquo;t lock you in.
						</p>
					</div>
				</div>

				<hr class="divider" />

				<!-- Step 3 -->
				<div class="step">
					<div class="step-number">3</div>
					<div class="step-body">
						<h3>Install the firmware</h3>

						<p><strong>For MeshCore:</strong></p>
						<ol style="color: var(--clr-light); padding-left: 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 1rem;">
							<li>
								Visit the <a
									href="https://flasher.meshcore.co.uk/"
									target="_blank"
									rel="noopener noreferrer">MeshCore Web Flasher</a
								> (Chrome/Edge required).
							</li>
							<li>Connect your device via USB and select your device model.</li>
							<li>Follow the on-screen instructions to flash the firmware*.</li>
							<li>
								Then, download the <strong>MeshCore app</strong> for your phone (<a
									href="https://apps.apple.com/gb/app/meshcore/id6742354151"
									target="_blank"
									rel="noopener noreferrer">iOS</a
								> /
								<a
									href="https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.liamcottle.meshcore.android"
									target="_blank"
									rel="noopener noreferrer">Android</a
								>) or use the desktop companion.
							</li>
						</ol>

						<p><strong>For Meshtastic:</strong></p>
						<ol style="color: var(--clr-light); padding-left: 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 1rem;">
							<li>
								Visit the <a
									href="https://flasher.meshtastic.org/"
									target="_blank"
									rel="noopener noreferrer">Meshtastic Web Flasher</a
								>.
							</li>
							<li>Connect your device via USB and select your device model.</li>
							<li>Choose the latest <strong>beta</strong> firmware.</li>
							<li>Follow the on-screen instructions to flash the firmware*.</li>
							<li>
								Download the <strong>Meshtastic app</strong> for your phone (<a
									href="https://apps.apple.com/app/meshtastic/id1586432531"
									target="_blank"
									rel="noopener noreferrer">iOS</a
								> /
								<a
									href="https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.geeksville.mesh"
									target="_blank"
									rel="noopener noreferrer">Android</a
								>).
							</li>
						</ol>
					</div>
				</div>

				<hr class="divider" />

				<!-- Step 4 -->
				<div class="step">
					<div class="step-number">4</div>
					<div class="step-body">
						<h3>Configure channels and connect</h3>
						<p>
							Open the app and pair it with your radio over Bluetooth or USB. Then join the Madison
							Mesh channel so your device can communicate with other local nodes.
							<br />
							<br />
							Make sure to select the <strong>US 915 MHz</strong> preset. We use the default settings
							for each platform, but make sure to enter Channel 20 on Meshtastic.
							<br />
							<br />
							Choose a fun name for your node. You can change this setting at any time.
							<br />
							<br />
							Once configured, place your node near a window or outside for the best range. Elevation
							makes a significant difference with LoRa antennas!
						</p>
					</div>
				</div>

				<hr class="divider" />

				<!-- Step 5 -->
				<div class="step">
					<div class="step-number">5</div>
					<div class="step-body">
						<h3>Say hello!</h3>
						<p>
							Once you&rsquo;re on the network, send a message on the public channel and introduce
							yourself. Then hop into the
							<a href="https://discord.gg/fd3JUZc2CN" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"
								>Discord</a
							>
							and let us know you&rsquo;re live: we&rsquo;d love to know where new nodes pop up!
						</p>
						<a
							href="https://discord.gg/fd3JUZc2CN"
							target="_blank"
							rel="noopener noreferrer"
							class="btn btn-primary"
						>
							Join the Discord &rarr;
						</a>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
			<div class="card-grid" style="margin-top: 1rem;">
				<div class="card" style="padding: 0.75rem;">
					<img
						src={handheldNodeGutsOrum.src}
						alt="Two community members with handheld mesh nodes"
						loading="lazy"
						style="display: block; width: 100%; height: auto; border-radius: 8px;"
					/>
				</div>
				<div class="card" style="padding: 0.75rem;">
					<img
						src={handheldNodeGuts2Orum.src}
						alt="Community members testing handheld nodes"
						loading="lazy"
						style="display: block; width: 100%; height: auto; border-radius: 8px;"
					/>
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>
	</div>
</Layout>
